3,0.04251406,0.04497163,-0.00135755,-0.08361761,-0.0174247,0.00258914,-0.00552491,0.0887709,0.17260157,0.01451501,0.00240516,-0.01476204,-0.05863179,0.06329709,0.0006473,0.02737223,0.02332693,0.05498695,0.02979503,0.01121663,0.07886492,0.0399739,-0.02929713,0.05919497,0.00174225,-0.02811503,-0.0015532,0.03439561,-0.01541024,0.01824948,0.09934791,0.06520502,-0.10678862,-0.01280374,-0.01200374,-0.00008839,-0.00490998,-0.00664037,0.06837133,0.11684813,0.00699514,0.04734857,-0.01795384,-0.01406552,0.01942678,-0.10894457,-0.00622359,-0.04678207,0.00385144,0.02629074,-0.01384389]}},"last_read":{"hash":"9803d7c60badf8cb9aeb6d6337c24d1823a5e14dfbf9d95830cb3c7968a2b0cf","at":1735544706434},"class_name":"SmartSource","outlinks":[{"title":"\n> **Sources:** [[\n\nEdgar Cayce: The Sleeping Prophet and His Visionary Insights\n\nEdgar Cayce (1877–1945) was an American mystic, healer, and psychic, known as the “Sleeping Prophet” due to his unique method of entering a trance state to give prophetic readings. Over the course of his life, Cayce provided over 14,000 readings, which addressed a wide range of topics, including health, reincarnation, spirituality, and earth sciences. His readings, though often controversial, have inspired a large following and continue to influence alternative healing practices and esoteric spiritual movements.\n\nEarly Life and Development of Psychic Abilities\n\nEdgar Cayce was born in Hopkinsville, Kentucky, and was raised in a religious environment. He had a strong connection to the Christian faith throughout his life, often attributing his abilities to a divine source. As a child, Cayce experienced several mystical and spiritual events, but it wasn’t until his early adulthood that he fully recognized and began to develop his psychic abilities.\n\nThe Birth of His Psychic Abilities\n\nAt the age of 24, Cayce suffered from a voice problem that rendered him temporarily unable to speak. In a desperate attempt to heal himself, he went into a trance and gave a diagnosis and prescription for his own condition. Remarkably, the treatment he prescribed worked, leading him to realize that he could access knowledge while in this altered state of consciousness.\n\nFrom that point on, Cayce began offering readings for others, answering questions about their health, spiritual life, and various other concerns while in a self-induced trance. His readings were given in a highly relaxed, almost sleep-like state, during which he claimed to be in direct contact with a higher spiritual consciousness or divine source.\n\nThe Cayce Readings: Key Themes and Insights\n\n1. Holistic Health and Healing\n\nOne of Cayce’s most significant contributions was his insights into holistic health and natural healing methods. He was a pioneer in mind-body medicine, advocating for the use of diet, herbs, exercise, and spiritual practices as a means of promoting well-being.\n\nHis health readings often included recommendations for natural treatments, such as dietary changes, herbal remedies, massage, and spiritual exercises. Cayce emphasized the importance of maintaining a balance between physical, mental, and spiritual health, as he believed the body could only heal when all aspects of a person were in harmony.\n\n2. Reincarnation and Karma\n\nCayce was one of the most prominent figures to advocate for the belief in reincarnation and karma within the framework of Western spirituality. His readings frequently spoke of past lives, with many individuals reportedly discovering information about their previous incarnations through his insights. He believed that each person’s present life was shaped by choices and actions from previous lives, and that karma—the law of cause and effect—was a guiding force.\n\nCayce also emphasized that soul development was ongoing through multiple lifetimes, and that individuals had the potential for growth and enlightenment by addressing unresolved issues from past lives.\n\n3. [[The Akashic Records","target":"\n> **Sources:** [[\n\nEdgar Cayce: The Sleeping Prophet and His Visionary Insights\n\nEdgar Cayce (1877–1945) was an American mystic, healer, and psychic, known as the “Sleeping Prophet” due to his unique method of entering a trance state to give prophetic readings. Over the course of his life, Cayce provided over 14,000 readings, which addressed a wide range of topics, including health, reincarnation, spirituality, and earth sciences. His readings, though often controversial, have inspired a large following and continue to influence alternative healing practices and esoteric spiritual movements.\n\nEarly Life and Development of Psychic Abilities\n\nEdgar Cayce was born in Hopkinsville, Kentucky, and was raised in a religious environment. He had a strong connection to the Christian faith throughout his life, often attributing his abilities to a divine source. As a child, Cayce experienced several mystical and spiritual events, but it wasn’t until his early adulthood that he fully recognized and began to develop his psychic abilities.\n\nThe Birth of His Psychic Abilities\n\nAt the age of 24, Cayce suffered from a voice problem that rendered him temporarily unable to speak. In a desperate attempt to heal himself, he went into a trance and gave a diagnosis and prescription for his own condition. Remarkably, the treatment he prescribed worked, leading him to realize that he could access knowledge while in this altered state of consciousness.\n\nFrom that point on, Cayce began offering readings for others, answering questions about their health, spiritual life, and various other concerns while in a self-induced trance. His readings were given in a highly relaxed, almost sleep-like state, during which he claimed to be in direct contact with a higher spiritual consciousness or divine source.\n\nThe Cayce Readings: Key Themes and Insights\n\n1. Holistic Health and Healing\n\nOne of Cayce’s most significant contributions was his insights into holistic health and natural healing methods. He was a pioneer in mind-body medicine, advocating for the use of diet, herbs, exercise, and spiritual practices as a means of promoting well-being.\n\nHis health readings often included recommendations for natural treatments, such as dietary changes, herbal remedies, massage, and spiritual exercises. Cayce emphasized the importance of maintaining a balance between physical, mental, and spiritual health, as he believed the body could only heal when all aspects of a person were in harmony.\n\n2. Reincarnation and Karma\n\nCayce was one of the most prominent figures to advocate for the belief in reincarnation and karma within the framework of Western spirituality. His readings frequently spoke of past lives, with many individuals reportedly discovering information about their previous incarnations through his insights. He believed that each person’s present life was shaped by choices and actions from previous lives, and that karma—the law of cause and effect—was a guiding force.\n\nCayce also emphasized that soul development was ongoing through multiple lifetimes, and that individuals had the potential for growth and enlightenment by addressing unresolved issues from past lives.\n\n3. [[The Akashic Records","line":3}],"last_import":{"mtime":1734863315000,"size":6524,"at":1735544706018,"hash":"9803d7c60badf8cb9aeb6d6337c24d1823a5e14dfbf9d95830cb3c7968a2b0cf"},"blocks":{"#":[1,63]}},"smart_blocks:Edgar Cayce.md#": {"path":null,"last_embed":{"hash":"9803d7c60badf8cb9aeb6d6337c24d1823a5e14dfbf9d95830cb3c7968a2b0cf","tokens":491},"embeddings":{"TaylorAI/bge-micro-v2":{"vec":[0.00161468,0.03189696,0.00502024,0.0482687,-0.06237707,0.02098599,0.01338858,-0.00979955,-0.02582734,0.00913493,-0.03803185,-0.0407749,-0.0298911,0.04383133,-0.00535372,0.00030034,0.0251956,0.06623837,-0.07144858,-0.02058338,0.07231461,-0.00849569,-0.04327722,-0.01685946,-0.03420037,-0.00747079,0.02480436,-0.07183319,-0.04999361,-0.13701664,-0.03746717,-0.00355463,-0.02509397,0.00488529,-0.00981077